<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-06T22:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-06T22:36:00-05:00" n="568" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d568">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 612.119/705</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-06T21:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 6, 1918, 9 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>677. My telegram No. 676, January 6, 2 p.m. Acting Minister for Foreign
                            Affairs informed me this afternoon that one of the <pb facs="0715" n="603" xml:id="pg_603"/> objects of Nieto’s proposed visit to the
                            United States is in connection with the pending conference.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>